<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">
    <!--
        Baseline suppressions for SkyStarter on Spring Boot 4.0.6 / Axon 5.1.0.

        Each CVE here was flagged by dependencyCheckAggregate (run with the
        no-configuration-cache and no-parallel flags) at CVSS >= 7.0. They
        live in transitive dependencies of Spring Boot / Axon that we don't
        pin directly. The fix path for each one is either: upgrade Spring
        Boot when a patch release ships, pin the transitive dep ourselves
        via constraints, or replace the dep entirely.

        The until date on each entry is the sunset: dependency-check will
        re-fail the build on that date if the CVE is still present, forcing
        a review. Bump the date only with a written rationale in
        docs/development.md "Accepted findings".
    -->

